# Template for registering a Hetzner Robot dedicated server as a bare-metal
# worker in the Syself management cluster.
#
# One CR per physical server. Apply into your org's namespace (same as the
# Cluster CR).
#
# Hetzner doesn't auto-discover servers — you tell Apalla which Robot IDs
# to take over. Syself then reinstalls the OS, bootstraps kubelet, and joins
# the node to the cluster.
#
# How to fill this in:
#   1. Rent a server via Hetzner Robot (robot.hetzner.com). Recommended for
#      the Tuist staging worker:
#        - AX41-NVMe or AX42  — 6-core Ryzen, 64 GB, 2× 512 GB NVMe (~€50/mo)
#        - EX44 as a fallback — 6-core i5-13500, 64 GB, 2× 512 GB NVMe
#      Put the new server in the same location as your cluster region
#      (fsn1 = Falkenstein).
#   2. Find the server ID: robot.hetzner.com → Servers → the server's URL
#      ends with #...=<id>; or `hcloud robot server list` if you use the CLI.
#   3. Find the root disk WWN: either leave `rootDeviceHints.wwn` empty and
#      read it from `kubectl describe hetznerbaremetalhost` after first
#      registration, or boot the server into Hetzner rescue and run
#      `lsblk -o NAME,WWN` against /dev/nvme0n1 (or sda for SATA boxes).
#   4. Label the host for the Cluster's workerHostSelectorBareMetal to match
#      (role=worker, cluster=tuist-staging).

apiVersion: infrastructure.cluster.x-k8s.io/v1beta1
kind: HetznerBareMetalHost
metadata:
  name: tuist-staging-worker-1
  namespace: REPLACE_ME_ORG_NAMESPACE
  labels:
    role: worker
    cluster: tuist-staging
spec:
  description: Tuist staging worker — Hetzner Robot dedicated (Falkenstein)
  serverID: REPLACE_ME_ROBOT_SERVER_ID
  rootDeviceHints:
    # Leave empty the first time — the Apalla status will surface the WWN
    # after first detection. Then fill it in to pin the install target.
    wwn: ""
  maintenanceMode: false
